article.headline: Patterson's 25 help Northwestern State defeat Houston Christian 64-57
article.description: — Addison Patterson's 25 points helped Northwestern State defeat Houston Christian 64-57 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Patterson's 25 help Northwestern State defeat Houston Christian 64-57
article.story: HOUSTON -- — Addison Patterson's 25 points helped Northwestern State defeat Houston Christian 64-57 on Saturday night. Patterson also added five rebounds and three steals for the Demons (5-5, 2-0 Southland Conference). Jon Sanders shot 5 of 9 from the field, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 5 for 5 from the line to add 17 points. Willie Williams shot 5 of 6 from the field to finish with 10 points, while adding 11 rebounds. Bryson Dawkins finished with 13 points for the Huskies (3-7, 1-1). D'Aundre Samuels added nine points for Houston Christian. Julian Mackey also had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
